Legolas in 10mm Scale

This model was inspired by the Lord of the Rings Fellowship of the Ring and the pewter model of Legolas produced by Games Workshop. It was produced for the LotR SBG but is in 10mm (epic) scale, not the standard 28mm scale. I know my sculpting isn't great but at that tiny scale, I think he gets the point across.

NOTE: This model has not been test printed.

A massive, sentient tree-like creature, often resembling an ancient oak or similar towering tree. Standing anywhere from 20 to 30 feet tall, its bark-covered body is as sturdy as stone, gnarled with age and wisdom. Demon character for warmaster both with and without supports using Schlossbauer's awesome twigblight. I initially wanted to use this as a greater demon, but seeing the size of the forest dragon treeman I needed another model to fill that role. I'm going to use this one as my general instead. Yes, it's obviously a tree thing, but just imagine what it looks like if you paint the torso bone-y and the arms/legs bloody (or find my post on the warmaster revolution facebook to see my actual paint job).

10mm demon army
See my collections for the other units; I have a unit for each of the roles in warmaster revolution and a couple of heroes. Note that this army does not inherently match one of the big four chaos gods by design, as I find them dreadfully boring.

Supports
The supports are auto generated by Prusa. Nothing much to it.

Why?
I just got a 3d printer and was looking to get into warmaster with some friends when I noticed that there is no ready to print demon army yet. Given my 0-level modelling skills I instead decided to use existing models to create the army; this unit is one of the outcomes of this project.

Disclaimer
To be sure: none of these models are actually mine. I am a complete hack blundering his way through blender; all I can do is resize models, fatten segments and add cylinders (you may spot some of my handiwork on other models, or here!).
